room_title: Escape room "First Settler" by Greenbrier Historical Society in Lewisburg
room_address: 934 N Jefferson St N, Lewisburg, WV 24901
room_description: The year is 1784 and you hear tell of lush and fertile lands west of the Appalachian Mountains in a new town named Lewisburg that has been formed near the Lewis Spring in Greenbrier County. You know the trip will be difficult, especially through the mountainous forests. Your goal is to make it to Lewisburg, establish a home, and survive on Virginia's western frontier.
